1. Move the pointer to the long bar at the top and confirm the webpage shows the correct address (it starts with “https” and includes the word “webcamtaxi”).  
2. Scroll down gently until you see a box showing the view you want (it has a picture and some text mentioning a place or city).  
3. Click that box once to open the live stream page.  
4. Wait a moment for the moving image to start displaying clearly.  
5. On your keyboard, press the button near the top row that begins with “Pr” (it grabs whatever is on your screen).  
6. Open any drawing or picture program on your computer.  
7. Press the keys together that start with “C” and “V” to place the grabbed image.  
8. Click the upper label that starts with “F” in that program.  
9. Pick the option that begins with “S” to store your file.  
10. Choose a name you like, then hit the option that starts with “O” to finish.
